I am reading now a book written by Roméo Dallaire «J'ai serré la main du diable». He explained his experience in Rwanda genocide. I do not know enough Burundi or Rwanda to make strong parallels, but it seems to me that:
1-there is no law and order now in Burundi;
2- killing with grenades;
3- killing of people inside the government (based on ethnic or/and a leader struggling for his life?);
4- no clear signal that it will be a sufficient and rapid international intervention;
5- presence of para military groups;
6- citizens are confused if the killings are coming from the government.
Some observers talked about Burundi like a civil war...like Roméo Dallaire wrote in his book.
What i am reading now from the book and the news is confuse me. Hope that i am wrong.

If by mass killing it mean « the act of murdering several or more people, typically simultaneously or over a relatively short period of time» then
1- an augmentation of people being killed in a period of times should indicate more probability that this situation occur (that doesn't mean that i don't believe in black swann)
2- an augmentation or a important relative number of people fleeing a territory should indicate that there is a danger enough to do so;
3- recent of antecedent of   mass killing should provide a another signal;
4- poly ethnic composition on a common territory with possibility of one or more ethnic group can be armed should be considered;
5- hate message from a leader group should be considered;
